description.narrative:
Vietnam Chamber of Commerce and Industry – Ho Chi Minh City Branch (VCCI HCM) is a national employers’ organization who is the representatives of business community. They have been providing supports enterprises in building capacity to reach the target of sustainable development.
In GRAISEA 2 project, VCCI HCM will provide support and facilitate market linkages between rice SMEs in the value chain with SSPs in Mekong Delta. They also develop strategy plan for supporting rice value chain in improving capacity and strategy which integrating inclusive business, CSR and WEE
In order to support rice and shrimp enterprises achieving the following objectives: “Within the agriculture and seafood value chains, market actors deliver opportunities that integrate small producers, promote women’s economic empowerment and support climate resilience”. The following outcomes are expected:
1. The private sector puts into practice inclusive models that support women’s economic empowerment and climate change resilience;
2. SMEs connect small producers fairlyto markets and build women’s economic empowerment;
3. MSIs at national and regional levels facilitate the wider use of business practices that support inclusivity women’s economic empowerment and climate change resilience (and influence government policy).
